title: What's News --  World-Wide
text:
Deliveries of Johnson & Johnson's Covid-19 vaccine doses throughout the U.S. are expected to drop by more than 80% next week, as the company grapples with manufacturing challenges.

---

Biden is seeking more funding for education, healthcare, research and renewable energy next year in a $1.52 trillion spending plan.

---

The president ordered a commission to study Supreme Court changes, such as adding seats.

---

George Floyd died because the officers restraining him put more strain on his heart than it could handle, a medical examiner testified.

---

The House Ethics panel said it has begun an investigation into allegations involving Rep. Matt Gaetz (R., Fla.), citing a host of alleged abuses.

---

Iran released a South Korean oil tanker that had been at the center of a dispute over punishing U.S. sanctions on Tehran.

---

Died: DMX, 50, influential rapper.
